RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 67. Maiden Claiming Purse 13000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SMALL SAILOR vied for the lead two wide down the backstretch, shook clear into the turn, widened into the lane then continued to extend the advantage through the final eighth while under a hand drive. MATLOCK was unhurried while off the inside, moved into the far turn while in the three path, was asked for more in late turn, got closest to the winner into the lane while drifting to the inside, could not gain on that one but stayed on to save the place spot. QUALITY DANCER unhurried while in the four path, was asked for more in late turn, came into the lane from the five path and gained on the place rival while drifting in a couple paths. MOMENT OF INSIGHT trailed early while near the inside, was under a drive when straightened into the backstretch, moved up the inside until the half-mile pole, was in tight, steadied and altered into the three path, was asked for more through the turn and never was a factor. FORTUNE raced four wide through the first turn, chased the pace from the three or four path into the far turn then was empty in the drive. MUD PUDDLE was in the two path throughout and tired. ALPHA LEA vied for the lead along the inside into the far turn then was done nearing the five-sixteenth pole.

ENTRY.NAME: Moment of Insight
ENTRY.COMMENT: trailed early, steadied 1/2, altered out, no factor

ENTRY.NAME: Matlock
ENTRY.COMMENT: unhurried early, 3path turn, asked 5/16, saved place

RACE.FOOTNOTES: GO MARGIE GO stalked the pace inside, bid at the three-eighths pole, shifted out four wide at the sixteenth pole, rallied and won under steady urging. L. A. WOMAN dueled inside of a rival, bid at the quarter pole, went clear but couldn't hold off the winner. SI CERTO was floated out seven wide going into the first turn, moved up to press the pace in the three path, bid at the quarter pole but was no match. EDGE OF TOWN dueled inside before fading in the stretch. DESIGNATED and GIGI'S WORLD were not factors.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 3 1M Turf CR: 82. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. RACE.FOOTNOTES: GET N TIPSY raced in mid-pack while in the two path, continued near the inside while moving closer through the turn, came into the lane from the four path, gained momentum once straightened, caught the leader just inside the sixteenth pole and drove clear. TAPERINEA raced into the first turn when under a strong hold while getting out a bit into the turn, moved to set the pace down the backstretch when under intermittent pressure, cleared into the lane, looked in good shape inside the eighth pole then could not hold the winner safe while saving the place spot. IZZY'S MONSTER was unhurried through the far turn when in the two path, shifted into the six path while entering the lane and was gaining to the end and missed the place spot. DIVINE EXCHANGE settled off the pace while off the inside, bid four wide into and through the turn, continued into the lane from the six path and moved up. AMAZING GAL tracked two path, came into the lane three wide then weakened through the lane. LUCKY SHORE never a factor while along the inside though the turns. FORGLO was unhurried while off the inside, moved three wide through the turn and never factored. PINK PARTY PANTS raced along the inside when not far back, continued along the rail into the lane and faded. PRESCIENCE raced in the four path through the far turn when near the back, swung into the lane from the seven or eight path and made no impact. NATIVE LION was in the four path through the first turn, chased the pace from the three or four path through the turn and was empty turning into the lane.

ENTRY.OWNER: Craftyhorse Racing LLC Schafer Homer and Sulzberger Jr Robert

DOUBLE TUFF stalked the pace in the four path, bid at the quarter pole but couldn't close late. BOURBON TEDDY led between rivals, bid clear at the three-eighths pole, dueled and gave way in the stretch. ROGER MCQUEEN threw his head in the gate and was back six lengths and had a bid at the quarter pole. HILLBILLY LOGIC pressed the pace between foes, then gave way on the turn. RACE.FOOTNOTES: MAJOR WAGER tracked the pacesetters while near the inside, guided to the three or four path into the lane, gained momentum inside the eighth pole and was up in time. JIMMY DAN was unhurried while off the inside, moved three wide through the turn when in mid-pack, came into the lane from the four or five path and was closing in too late. MILITARY FORCE set the pace while near the inside, vied with another down the backstretch, was still under pressure through the turn, cleared into the lane, had his largest advantage with an eighth to go then was caught near the wire and just lost the place spot as well. PARKLAND was in the two path through the turn when never far back, straightened in the four path, was steadied near the eighth pole when a rival drifted over and he lost his path, reengaged and finished with good energy. VINTAGE VINYL saved ground into the lane, had an open rail for the drive and needed more. MAJOR SPARKS raced in the two path into and through the far turn, angled into the five path for the drive and was gaining belatedly. J'S NAUGHTY BOY was near the inside into the far turn, raced in the two or three path in late turn, straightened in the six path and showed interest too late. TOPF ROAD RULES chased the pace into the backstretch, vied for the lead into the turn, continued to chase the pace into the lane then faded. STORM'S REFLECTION saved ground into the lane and lacked a response. Raced was hand-timed due to a timer malfunction.

ENTRY.OWNER: Southwest Racing Stables Inc and Murphy Bruce
